{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"agent_message","text":"The first experiments identify the core new mechanic. Color 9 is the controlled 5×5 avatar (actions 1–4 translate it by one tile; 5 is contextual), while color 14 is an autonomous helper in a disconnected upper corridor. The helper advances along its own route once per successful avatar move, independent of direction; blocked moves do not advance it. Pure movement explores 17 avatar positions and cannot win, so level 6 requires committing paths with USE to preserve changes caused jointly by the two regions. I’m now isolating those persistent post-reset changes from mere actor motion."}}
